# Sections in a docker file
# FROM: base of the minimal operating system. TLDR alpine debian:jesse
# ENV - environmental variable: prefered way to inject keys/values/arguements because they work everywhere.
# RUN - runs commands /shell scripts in the container. Can have multiple RUN commands execution goes top down.
# EXPOSE: makes ports availble on the docker virtual network. By default no ports are exposed.
# CMD final command that is run when the container runs.
